The paper studies load balancing problems, which are typically studied in the computer science subfield of data structures (cs.DS). The ball recycling game is also closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG), as it involves maximizing a recycling rate through a specific strategy. The game also models memory-access heuristics in databases, which falls under the subfield of databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper discusses the stationary distribution of the game, which is a concept commonly studied in the subfield of control systems (cs.SY).
